This paper focuses on reducing the prediction time of a trained black-box structured classifier without losing accuracy. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), natural language processing (cs.CL), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), computer vision (cs.CV), and cryptography and security (cs.CR) as these sub-categories are closely related to the topic of structured output prediction.
